Ah, your problem is that `inputData.rawNumber` is already a string. Resulting in this:

```js
&#39;100988765&#39;.toString(16) // =&gt; &quot;100988765&quot;
```

Instead, parse it into a number first:

```js
const steamIdAsNum = parseInt(inputData.steam, 10)
return {steamhex: steamIdAsNum.toString(16)}
```

